
This lab demonstrates the use of Hugging Face, Sentence Transformers, FastAI, and Kaggle datasets for performing various Natural Language Processing (NLP) tasks.
The experiment includes **sentiment analysis, text summarization, machine translation, sentence embeddings, and semantic search** using pre-trained models. 
Additionally, a **text classification model was trained on the IMDb dataset using FastAI** to classify movie reviews as positive or negative. 
The results were saved and evaluated to understand how modern AI frameworks simplify NLP tasks.
